.TH "omap4_prminst_is_hardreset_asserted" 9 "omap4_prminst_is_hardreset_asserted" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap4_prminst_is_hardreset_asserted \- read the HW reset line state of submodules contained in the hwmod module
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap4_prminst_is_hardreset_asserted
.BI "(u8 shift "  ","
.BI "u8 part "  ","
.BI "s16 inst "  ","
.BI "u16 rstctrl_offs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "shift" 12
register bit shift corresponding to the reset line to check
.IP "part" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "inst" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "rstctrl_offs" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 1 if the (sub)module hardreset line is currently asserted,
0 if the (sub)module hardreset line is not currently asserted, or
-EINVAL upon parameter error.
